The Y maze has three identical opaque arms (40 cm-long, 10 cm-wide, and 15 cm-high). We conducted the Y maze test as previously described [60]. Briefly, mice were habituated the testing room for 60 min and placed in the distal end of one arm. The mice were allowed to freely explore for 5 min without any interference. The monitor system (EthoVision XT 12) recorded the locus of mice movement, while the sequence of entries was manually recorded and analyzed by the experimenter. The alternation ratio was calculated as follows:
